---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'The Other Door';
const date = '2026';
---

<Layout title={`${title} — your name`} description="A poem about dying as the other crossing — the one you already survived.">
  <article class="poem-page">
    <h1 class="poem-page-title">{title}</h1>
    <div class="poem-page-date">{date}</div>

    <div class="poem-body">
      <p>What if you've already done this?</p>

      <p>What if dying is just

the other door —

the one you came through

before you knew

you were coming,

before you had a name for the light

or a word for the cold

or a body to hold

all that arriving in?</p>

      <p>You weren't afraid then.</p>

      <p>Think about that.

You weren't afraid then.</p>

      <p>You crossed the whole impossible distance

between nothing and here —

between silence and first breath and fear —

and you didn't even know to grieve it,

didn't know to clutch the dark and say

wait,

wait, I need another minute,

I don't know what's on the other side —</p>

      <p>you just
came.</p>

      <p>And maybe that's what dying is.

Not an ending.

Not the lights going out in an empty house.

Maybe it's the forgetting

you already survived once —

the same crossing,

the same unmarked water,

the same darkness that turned out to hold you

before you were anything

that could be held.</p>

      <p>We call it death

like it's the first time.</p>

      <p>Like we haven't been

to the edge of the everything

and stepped off

and arrived

and forgotten

and become

and loved

and lost

and clutched this life

like it's the only one we know how to live —</p>

      <p>because it is.

Because we forgot.</p>

      <p>But the soul remembers

what the mind can't hold —

that before is after,

that the cold is also warmth arriving,

that the last breath out

is just the first breath in

for whatever comes next,</p>

      <p>whatever you become

when you stop being this —</p>

      <p>this specific, suffering,

beautiful, unfinished,

reaching
you.</p>

      <p>And it won't be loss.</p>

      <p>It'll be the way it felt

before you knew you'd arrived —</p>

      <p>weightless,

formless,

and completely

unafraid.</p>
    </div>

    <nav class="poem-nav">
      <a href="/poems/fluent-in-fine">← Fluent in Fine</a>
      <span></span>
    </nav>
  </article>
</Layout>
